ning for lost loved ones.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAnger in literature. 0aCharacters and characteristics in literature. 0aCreativity in literature. 0aEmotions in literature. 0aGrief in literature. 0aPsychoanalysis and literaturezEngland. 0aPsychological fiction, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBerman, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311071692440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814743973.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814743973zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814743973/original  a978-3-11-071692-4 New York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA